## Approach

I used the mathematical sum formula to solve this problem efficiently. 
First, I calculated the expected sum of all numbers from 0 to n using the formula n × (n + 1) / 2,
where n is the length of the array. This gives the sum if no number were missing.

Next, I traversed the given array once and calculated the actual sum of all the elements present in the array.
Since exactly one number is missing, the actual sum will always be smaller than the expected sum.

Finally, I subtracted the actual sum from the expected sum. The difference between these two sums is the missing number,
which is then returned as the answer.

## Time Complexity
   O(n)

## Space Complexity
   O(1).
